.\" Man page generated from: ./evilcandy --help
.TH EVILCANDY 1 "2026-04-19" "EvilCandy" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
evilcandy \- EvilCandy interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B evilcandy
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.RI [ INFILE ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B evilcandy
runs the EvilCandy interpreter.
.PP
EvilCandy is an object-oriented programming language.
.PP
If no input file is specified,
.B evilcandy
can be run as a REPL.  It can also read input from a pipe or run a script
from a file.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-d
Disassembly mode.
.TP
.BI \-c " STRING"
Interpret
.I STRING
instead of a file.
.TP
.BI \-e " STRING"
Same as
.BR \-c .
.TP
.B \-V
Print version and quit.
.TP
.BI \-I " DIR"
Add an import path.
If multiple \-I options are used,
they should be requested in decreasing order of priority.
.TP
.B \-h
Print help and quit.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Same as
.BR \-V .
.TP
.B \-\-help
Same as
.BR \-h .
.TP
.B \-\-check
Compile but do not execute.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
REPL mode:
.B evilcandy
.TP
Pipe mode:
.B cat FILE | evilcandy
.TP
Script mode:
.B evilcandy FILE
